timation, in sample complexity that\nscales log-linearly with respect to the number $p$ of parameters. In addition,\nwe propose and analyze a novel compressive algorithm for simulating and kriging\nof GRFs. The complexity (work and memory vs. accuracy) of these three\nalgorithms scales near-optimally in terms of the number of parameters $p$ of\nthe sample-wise approximation of the GRF in Sobolev scales.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 7 Mar 2021 18:45:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-09"}
